    <h2 id="supported-content" class="docs-h3">Supported Content</h2>

    <p>There are a handful of sub-components that come
    with the header. These can be mix and matched from the
    following as is needed.</p>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>header-meta-menu</code></li>
        <li><code>header-brand</code></li>
        <li><code>header-burger</code></li>
        <li><code>header-search</code></li>
        <li><code>nav</code></li>
        <li><code>header-item</code> for <code>btn</code> or other elements</li>
      </ul>
    </p>

    <p>The provided sub-components are described in the
    following sections.</p>

    <h3 class="docs-h4">Meta menu</h3>

    <p>The meta menu is always located in the upper part of the
    header. It allows you to interconnect separate parts
    of your app or even link to other related apps. It is used
    with the <code>.header-meta-menu</code> block.</p>

    <header class="header">
      <div class="header-meta">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <nav class="header-meta-menu">
            <ul class="header-meta-menu-list">
              <li class="header-meta-menu-item">
                <a href="#" class="header-meta-menu-link">Individuals</a>
              </li>
              <li class="header-meta-menu-item">
                <a href="#" class="header-meta-menu-link">Small Businesses</a>
              </li>
              <li class="header-meta-menu-item">
                <a href="#" class="header-meta-menu-link">Businesses</a>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <h3 class="docs-h4">Brand</h3>

    <p>The brand block allows you to brand your app so people can set
    it apart from others more easily.
    Use the <code>.header-brand</code> for that.
    The element should be a link, so you can link back to your home page.
    Make sure that there is only one node in the brand component.</p>

    <header class="header">
      <div class="header-main">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <a href="#" class="header-brand">
            <span>
              <strong>AXA</strong>
              <br />
              <span>Strategic Ventures</span>
            </span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <p>You can also provide an image like a logo by simply replacing
    any text and adding an image to the <code>.header-brand</code>
    item.</p>

    <header class="header">
      <div class="header-main">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <a href="#" class="header-brand">
            <img class="header-brand-image" src="{{relative '/images/axa.svg'}}" />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <h3 class="docs-h4">Burger</h3>

    <p>The burger is a well recognized pattern to open a
    menu drawer and should be placed in the main part of the header.
    It is created using the <code>.header-burger</code> block. Make
    sure it is placed correctly on the side where the drawer is
    going to appear.</p>

    <header class="header">
      <div class="header-main">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <a href="#" class="header-burger">
            <span class="header-burger-line"></span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <h3 class="docs-h4">Search</h3>

    <p>The search is an interactive element and always expands
    to the left. It is created using the <code>.header-search</code> block.
    This is why it always has to be on the right side.</p>

    <header class="header">
      <div class="header-main">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <form class="header-search float-xs-right" data-search="header">
            <div class="header-search-dunno">
              <input type="text" class="header-search-input" name="q" placeholder="Search the entire axa.com" />
              <button type="submit" class="header-search-button">
                <span class="sr-only">Search</span>
                <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-search" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              </button>
            </div>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

